Class Ingredient

java.lang.Object
com.example.models.Ingredient
public class Ingredient extends Object
Model representing an ingredient in inventory.

Tracks id, name, stock quantity, measurement unit, reorder threshold, and a computed status based on stock vs reorder level.

Author:
Dayo Bamgbelu

    • Ingredient

      public Ingredient(int ingredientId, String ingredientName, int stockQuantity, String unitMeasurement, int reorderLevel)
      Construct a new Ingredient.
      Parameters:
      ingredientId - the unique id (0 when not yet persisted)
      ingredientName - display name for the ingredient
      stockQuantity - current stock quantity
      unitMeasurement - unit measurement (e.g., g, ml, units)
      reorderLevel - threshold at which stock is considered low
